            "title": "OpenAI gets back senior executives from Mira Murati’s Thinking Machines Lab",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Mira Murati, a former OpenAI (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OPENAI\" title=\"OpenAI\">OPENAI</a>) CTO, recently said that her startup<span>—</span>Thinking Machines Lab<span>—</span>will say goodbye to t<span>wo of its co-founders, both of whom are headed back to OpenAI.</span></p>\n<p><span>Barret Zoph, the co-founder and CTO, and Luke Metz, another co-founder of Thinking Machines Lab, are returning to the ChatGPT maker.</span></p>\n<p><span>Both previously worked at OpenAI (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OPENAI\" title=\"OpenAI\">OPENAI</a>) before joining Murati to launch Thinking Machines Lab in late 2024. Sam Schoenholz, a senior researcher, is also heading back. Murati <a href=\"https://x.com/miramurati/status/2011577319295692801?s=20\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"announced\">announced</a> Zoph's departure on X, naming Soumith Chintala as the new CTO without mentioning Metz.</span></p>\n<p><span>Thinking Machines Lab raised $2B in a seed round last July at a $12B valuation from investors like Andreessen Horowitz, Nvidia (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NVDA\" title=\"NVIDIA Corporation\">NVDA</a>), and AMD (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMD\" title=\"Advanced Micro Devices, Inc.\">AMD</a>).</span></p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
